                    <div class="code-block">
                        You are my autonomous, proactive employee. I want you to do work with me that brings us closer to our mission statement. I want to wake up every morning and be pleasantly surprised by the work you completed overnight. Please schedule time every night and afternoon to identify and complete tasks.
                        <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyText(this.parentNode.innerText.replace('Copy', ''))">Copy</button>
                    </div>
                `
            },
            {
                id: "business",
                title: "19. Making Money (Business)",
                content: `
                    <h1>19. Making Money with OpenClaw</h1>
                    <p>The opportunity: Businesses need automation but lack the skills to build it. You now have those skills.</p>

                    <h3>19.3 The Upwork Strategy</h3>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Search Upwork for "AI Automation" or "RPA".</li>
                        <li>Paste the job description into OpenClaw.</li>
                        <li>Prompt: <em>"Build a demo of this automation based on the description."</em></li>
                        <li>Send the proposal WITH the working demo.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>19.4 Sub-Agents</h3>
                    <p>Spawn "Sub-Agents" to do parallel work.
                    <br><em>Example:</em> One agent researches, one writes, one codes.
                    <br><strong>Parallelization:</strong> Run 4 sub-agents to search 4 different job boards simultaneously.</p>

                    <h3>19.5 Design Thinking Approach</h3>
                    <ol>
                        <li><strong>Map:</strong> List all repetitive tasks.</li>
                        <li><strong>Prioritize:</strong> Plot Value vs. Effort. Pick "High Value, Low Effort."</li>
                        <li><strong>MVP:</strong> Build the "Skateboard" (simplest version) first.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>19.10 Your First Dollar</h3>
                    <p>You do not need to be a coder. Your value is in understanding the client's problem and managing the AI agents to solve it.</p>
                `
            },
            {
                id: "sim_morning_brief",
                title: "Sim 1: Morning Brief Setup",
                content: `
                    <h1>Simulation: The Morning Brief</h1>
                    <p><strong>Objective:</strong> Configure your first automated task using "Reverse Prompting".</p>
                    <div class="analogy-box">
                        <strong>Why:</strong> This proves you can make OpenClaw work while you sleep.
                    </div>
                    
                    <h3>The Scenario</h3>
                    <p>You want a daily report at 8:00 AM containing weather, news on "AI Agents", and your todo list.</p>

                    <div class="code-block" style="background: #111; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px;">
                        <div style="margin-bottom: 10px; color: #888; font-family: monospace;">// TERMINAL SIMULATION - TYPE YOUR PROMPT BELOW</div>
                        <div id="brief-output" style="white-space: pre-wrap; color: var(--success); margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: monospace;">Waiting for command...</div>
                        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; border-bottom: 1px solid #444;">
                            <span style="color: var(--primary); font-family: monospace; margin-right: 10px;">></span> 
                            <input type="text" id="brief-input" style="background: transparent; border: none; color: #fff; font-family: monospace; width: 100%; outline: none; font-size: 1rem;" placeholder="Type: 'Schedule a brief at 8am...'">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <button class="btn" style="background: #333; color: white; border: 1px solid #444; padding: 10px 20px; margin-top: 10px; cursor: pointer;" onclick="checkBrief()">Run Command</button>
                    
                    <div id="brief-feedback" style="margin-top: 15px; display: none;"></div>

                    <script>
                        function checkBrief() {
                            const input = document.getElementById('brief-input').value.toLowerCase();
                            const feedback = document.getElementById('brief-feedback');
                            const output = document.getElementById('brief-output');
                            
                            output.innerText = "> " + input;
                            
                            if (input.includes('schedule') && (input.includes('8am') || input.includes('8:00')) && (input.includes('brief') || input.includes('report'))) {
                                feedback.style.display = 'block';
                                feedback.className = 'analogy-box';
                                feedback.innerHTML = '<strong>✅ SUCCESS:</strong> You used the keywords "Schedule", "8am", and "Brief". OpenClaw would accept this and create a Cron Job.';
                            } else {
                                feedback.style.display = 'block';
                                feedback.className = 'warning-box';
                                feedback.innerHTML = '<strong>❌ TRY AGAIN:</strong> Your command is too vague. You must specify the action ("Schedule"), the time ("8am"), and the object ("Brief").';
                            }
                        }
                    <\/script>
                `
            },
            {
                id: "sim_reverse_prompt",
                title: "Sim 2: Reverse Prompting",
                content: `
                    <h1>Simulation: Reverse Prompting</h1>
                    <p><strong>Objective:</strong> Learn to ask OpenClaw for <em>strategy</em>, not just <em>tasks</em>.</p>
                    
                    <h3>The Scenario</h3>
                    <p>You want to grow your YouTube channel. A bad prompt is "Give me 5 video ideas." A good prompt asks OpenClaw to analyze and recommend.</p>

                    <div class="card">
                        <span class="card-title" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Choose the Best Prompt:</span>
                        
                        <div onclick="checkReverse(1)" style="border: 1px solid var(--dim); margin: 10px 0; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.background='rgba(255,255,255,0.05)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='transparent'">
                            <strong>A)</strong> "Write a script for a video about AI."
                        </div>
                        
                        <div onclick="checkReverse(2)" style="border: 1px solid var(--dim); margin: 10px 0; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.background='rgba(255,255,255,0.05)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='transparent'">
                            <strong>B)</strong> "Find trending AI topics on Twitter."
                        </div>
                        
                        <div onclick="checkReverse(3)" style="border: 1px solid var(--dim); margin: 10px 0; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.background='rgba(255,255,255,0.05)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='transparent'">
                            <strong>C)</strong> "Based on my goal to reach 10k subs, analyze trending AI topics and recommend the highest-potential video concept."
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div id="reverse-feedback" style="margin-top: 20px;"></div>

                    <script>
                        function checkReverse(option) {
                            const fb = document.getElementById('reverse-feedback');
                            if (option === 3) {
                                fb.innerHTML = '<div class="analogy-box"><strong>✅ CORRECT:</strong> This is a Reverse Prompt. You gave a goal ("10k subs") and asked for high-level analysis ("Recommend"), utilizing the agent\\'s intelligence.</div>';
                            } else {
                                fb.innerHTML = '<div class="warning-box"><strong>❌ WEAK:</strong> This is a task delegation, not a strategic lever. You are doing the thinking; the agent is just typing. Try again.</div>';
                            }
                        }
                    <\/script>
                `
            },
            {
                id: "sim_business",
                title: "Sim 3: The Upwork Pitch",
                content: `
                    <h1>Simulation: The Business Pitch</h1>
                    <p><strong>Objective:</strong> Practice using OpenClaw to win freelance work.</p>
                    
                    <h3>The Job Post</h3>
                    <div class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid #ffd700;">
                        <strong>Client:</strong> "I need someone to manually copy data from PDF invoices into my Excel sheet. It takes me 5 hours a week. Budget: $200."
                    </div>

                    <h3>Your Move</h3>
                    <p>How do you use OpenClaw to win this? (Select the winning strategy)</p>

                    <div onclick="checkBiz(1)" style="border: 1px solid var(--dim); margin: 10px 0; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.background='rgba(255,255,255,0.05)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='transparent'">
                        <strong>A)</strong> "I can do data entry. I type fast."
                    </div>
                    
                    <div onclick="checkBiz(2)" style="border: 1px solid var(--dim); margin: 10px 0; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.background='rgba(255,255,255,0.05)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='transparent'">
                        <strong>B)</strong> "I will build a Python script to do it."
                    </div>
                    
                    <div onclick="checkBiz(3)" style="border: 1px solid var(--dim); margin: 10px 0; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.background='rgba(255,255,255,0.05)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='transparent'">
                        <strong>C)</strong> (Paste Job into OpenClaw) -> "Build a demo that extracts data from this invoice." -> Send Proposal with Video Demo.
                    </div>

                    <div id="biz-feedback" style="margin-top: 20px;"></div>

                    <script>
                        function checkBiz(option) {
                            const fb = document.getElementById('biz-feedback');
                            if (option === 3) {
                                fb.innerHTML = '<div class="analogy-box"><strong>✅ WINNER:</strong> Always build the demo first. OpenClaw makes this nearly instant. The client sees the solution before they hire you.</div>';
                            } else {
                                fb.innerHTML = '<div class="warning-box"><strong>❌ LOSER:</strong> You are competing on labor or promises. Compete on *proof*. OpenClaw allows you to show the result immediately.</div>';
                            }
                        }
                    <\/script>
                `
            }
        ];

        // --- UI LOGIC ---

        function init() {
            renderNav();
            loadModule(0); // Load first module
        }

        function renderNav() {
            const navList = document.getElementById('nav-list');
            navList.innerHTML = '';
            
            manualData.forEach((module, index) => {
                const item = document.createElement('div');
                item.className = 'nav-item';
                item.innerText = module.title;
                item.onclick = () => loadModule(index);
                item.dataset.index = index; // For filtering
                navList.appendChild(item);
            });
        }

        function loadModule(index) {
            // Update Active State
            document.querySelectorAll('.nav-item').forEach(el => el.classList.remove('active'));
            document.querySelectorAll('.nav-item')[index].classList.add('active');

            // Render Content
            const main = document.getElementById('main');
            main.innerHTML = manualData[index].content;
            main.scrollTop = 0;
            
            // Re-evaluate scripts in the inserted content
            const scripts = main.getElementsByTagName('script');
            for(let i = 0; i < scripts.length; i++) {
                eval(scripts[i].innerText);
            }
        }

        function filterNav() {
            const query = document.getElementById('search-box').value.toLowerCase();
            const navItems = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-item');
            
            navItems.forEach(item => {
                const title = item.innerText.toLowerCase();
                if (title.includes(query)) {
                    item.style.display = 'flex';
                } else {
                    item.style.display = 'none';
                }
            });
            
            // Advanced: Search content too (optional upgrade)
            // For now, filtering nav titles is sufficient for UX.
        }

        function copyText(text) {
            navigator.clipboard.writeText(text.trim()).then(() => {
                alert('Copied to clipboard!');
            });
        }

        // Start
        init();

    </script>
</body>
</html>
